        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 1:55PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 154 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Mountain Park to Siloam to near King.
Movement was southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fairview...
Dobson...
King...
Pilot Mountain State Park...
Level Cross...
Rockford...
and Siloam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
